task.summary: Switched IDE from VS to PyCharm and adjusted git repository structure accordingly
ClassificationExperimentBase wrapping mnist module to download and parse the MNSIT data and skeleton for the first BinaryClassificationExperiment concrete implementation
Extended BinaryClassificationExperiment with binary classification of MNIST images (5 and not 5) based on Stochastic Gradient Descent Classifier
Introduced performance metrics in binary classification (confusion matrix, precision, sensitivity and f1 score)
White box-type experiment with a linear regression model fitting based on normal equation
Added training set fit based on Batch Gradient Descent to the LinearRegressionExperiment
Added fitting based on Stochastic Grading Descent to the white-box LinearRegressionExperiment
Added fitting based on Mini-Batch Grading Descent to the white-box LinearRegressionExperiment
Added export list to all packages (facade for simpler imports)
Train LogisticRegression with all features of iris dataset in LogisticRegressionExperiment
Various minor adjustments to PreprocessingExperiment and BinaryClassificationExperiment
Added plots (vector instances with different colors for labels) to linear and non-linear SVM classification experiments
Added more experiments to linear and non-linear SVM classification and decision region plotting via mlxtend
Added SGD Classifier to NonLinearSvmClassificationExperiment and confusion matrix computing to compare Random Forest, SGD and K-Nearest Neighbours
Added linear and non-linear SVM regression experiments
Added basic multiclass predictions (classes probabilities and class name) to DecisionTreeVisualizationExperiment
Adjusted main module to be able to pass the experiment to run as a command line argument
Added dockerfile and .dockerignore for building a Docker image
